{
  "texts": [
    "GraphAide provides a simple API to ingest datasets into the vector database and persist them locally for future use.",
    "The novelty of GraphAide lies in its use of a graph database to store additional structural information.",
    "GraphAide's API offers domain-specific graph modeling and graph persistence functionality.",
    "The graph database is used in subsequent phases to enhance the performance of retrieval operations.",
    "Generation of an ontology-guided Knowledge Graph (KG) from heterogeneous sources is one of the key contributions of GraphAide."
  ]
}